\par 
\par "I like the French people, of whom there are lots--both natives and exiles--very much. They're appreciative, friendly, jolly, well dressed--even though almost in rags in some cases--and even cleaner than some
 people I could name. They also know how to cook when there's anything around to practice on." (Force 141, APO 512).
\par 
\par "Last Monday I was invited by some Spanish people to dine with them. It was a very nice meal. People here are very fine, especially the Spanish-speaking people who treat me wonderfully because I speak Spanish." (3487th Ord. Co., APO 512).
\par 
\par "Yes I did go out with some of the French dames and boy what a time I had." (1st General Depot, APO 698).
\par 
