\par "Lately we have seen many prisoners both German and Itali
an. They are a sorry looking bunch of men. The Italians are friendly and seem happy about their capture. On the other hand, the Germans are arrogant and quite disillusioned. One officer in particular stood out above the rest. He marched with his head high
, shoulders back, and eyes to the front. He was a fine looking soldier, and drew much comment from the onlookers." (36 Engrs., APO 698).
